<script id="cross-stitch" type="text/x-custom-template">
  <div class="lacingSteps-inner">
    <div class="lacingSteps-close"></div>
    <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionColumn [ grid--justifyCenter grid--center med-grid--justifySpaceAround med-grid--flexDirectionRow ]">
    
      <div class="lacingSteps-images" data-images-slideshow>
        <div>
          <img alt="" src="{{'style--theCrosStitch_1.svg' | asset_url }}">
        </div>
        <div>
          <img alt="" src="{{'style--theCrosStitch_2.svg' | asset_url }}">
        </div>
        <div>
          <img alt="" src="{{'style--theCrosStitch_3.svg' | asset_url }}">
        </div>
        <div>
          <img alt="" src="{{'style--theCrosStitch_4.svg' | asset_url }}">
        </div>
      </div>
    
      <ul class="lacingSteps-details   grid  grid--center  grid--justifyCenter" data-steps-slideshow>
        <li class="lacingSteps-step">
          <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionRow grid--top  med-grid--flexDirectionColumn">
            <span class="lacingSteps-number">01</span>
            <p class="lacingSteps-body">Your meemaw’s cross stitch, this is not. Begin with your Whiskers coming out of the bottom eyelets, away from the tongue.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="lacingSteps-step">
          <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionRow grid--top  med-grid--flexDirectionColumn">
            <span class="lacingSteps-number">02</span>
            <p class="lacingSteps-body">Jump three eyelets above, cross over and insert. Bring each lace out of the eyelet above, keep them on their same side.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li  class="lacingSteps-step">
          <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionRow grid--top  med-grid--flexDirectionColumn">
            <span class="lacingSteps-number">03</span>
            <p class="lacingSteps-body">Repeat but upside down. Drop your laces down three eyelets and insert, being sure to cross over and weave as you do so. Pull the laces out through the empty eyelets above.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li  class="lacingSteps-step">
          <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionRow grid--top  med-grid--flexDirectionColumn">
            <span class="lacingSteps-number">04</span>
            <p class="lacingSteps-body">Jump three eyelets one last time, crossing over and weaving again. Now you can cross this one off your list.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</script>


<script id="hypotenuse" type="text/x-custom-template">
  <div class="lacingSteps-inner">
    <div class="lacingSteps-close"></div>
    <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionColumn [ grid--justifyCenter grid--center med-grid--justifySpaceAround med-grid--flexDirectionRow ]">
    
      <div class="lacingSteps-images" data-images-slideshow>
        <div>
          <img alt="" src="{{'style--hypotenuse_1.svg' | asset_url }}">
        </div>
        <div>
          <img alt="" src="{{'style--hypotenuse_2.svg' | asset_url }}">
        </div>
        <div>
          <img alt="" src="{{'style--hypotenuse_3.svg' | asset_url }}">
        </div>
        <div>
          <img alt="" src="{{'style--hypotenuse_4.svg' | asset_url }}">
        </div>
      </div>
    
      <ul class="lacingSteps-details  grid  grid--center  grid--justifyCenter" data-steps-slideshow>
        <li class="lacingSteps-step">
          <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionRow grid--top  med-grid--flexDirectionColumn">
            <span class="lacingSteps-number">01</span>
            <p class="lacingSteps-body">If you’re angling for a new look, here it is. Start by inserting your Whiskers into the bottom eyelets towards the tongue. Pull the right side of the laces through the eyelet above. </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="lacingSteps-step">
          <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionRow grid--top  med-grid--flexDirectionColumn">
            <span class="lacingSteps-number">02</span>
            <p class="lacingSteps-body">Cross the left side of the laces diagonally over to the right side and pull out through the next empty eyelet. Then, take the side that was originally on the right and cross it straight left into the empty eyelet and insert it.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li  class="lacingSteps-step">
          <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionRow grid--top  med-grid--flexDirectionColumn">
            <span class="lacingSteps-number">03</span>
            <p class="lacingSteps-body">Repeat. Cross the new left side over diagonally and into the empty eyelet on the right. Cross the lace that was originally on the right side straight over and into the empty eyelet on the left. Repeat again.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li  class="lacingSteps-ste">
          <div class="grid grid--flexDirectionRow grid--top  med-grid--flexDirectionColumn">
            <span class="lacingSteps-number">04</span>
            <p class="lacingSteps-body">Once you’ve hypontenused all you can, finish with one final cross to the right side. On the left, pull the lace through up through the empty eyelet above. When lacing your next shoes, you can flip directions for a mirrored look or keep them the same for a repeating vibe. We trust you to make the right decision.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    
    </div>
  </div>
</script>



